OL,3,CPolice offer 'empty apology' to
OL,4,CHillsborough parents
OL,6,FThe Hillsborough Independent Panel and
OL,7,Fsubsequent inquests found that the
OL,8,Fsuggestion victims lost consciousness
OL,9,Fwithin seconds was flawed.
OL,11,FThe assumption ` dubbed "the 30-second
OL,12,Frule" ` was used in post-disaster
OL,13,Fcases and presumed victims lost
OL,14,Fconsciousness almost immediately,
OL,15,Fincluding in a 1990s test case brought
OL,16,Fby the Hicks family.
OL,18,FTheir claim for damages against South
OL,19,FYorkshire Police was dismissed at
OL,20,Fmultiple levels, culminating in a
OL,21,Frejection by the House of Lords.
